  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cyclone Idai Phase 2-ACT-DKH</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Outcomes:
- Target communities have improved access to potable water and good health and hygiene information and services 
- Target communities have improved capacity to prepare for, anticipate and deal with the effects of disaster and climate change
- Target communities have improved access to community based psychosocial support and GBV awareness information and services</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve access to potable water, spring protection, boreholes rehabilitation and community wells upgrading will be undertaken in the target district. This will be followed by training and equipping of water point committees. Volunteers will be identified in the target communities and trained on health and hygiene promotion. These will lead the establishment of Community Health Clubs. All activities will fight the risk of disease outbreaks.

The resulting disaster risk management plans will have the following components; contingency/preparedness, early warning and a disaster risk reduction. The latter will lead to the development of structural and non-structural measures which will include gully reclamation, slope improvement, afforestation and DRR awareness raising.

MeDRA brings their experience through training CBPSS facilitators and engagement of PSS stakeholders in mapping a referral pathways.</narrative>
  </description>
